  <p>Your task is a simple one, create a type-as-you-go search for customers.</p>

  <h3>Requirements</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Create a new route to search for customers.</li>
    <li>Use ember-data to create models that expose customer data to the application.</li>
    <li>You must be able to search all three fields.</li>
    <li>How the results are displayed and styling rules are, for this exercise, up to you.</li>
    <li>Tests are not required. Which isn't to say you shouldn't write them. How many tests? Up to you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Note:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your ability to deal with open ended requriements is part of the test.</li>
    <li>Your ability to research problems and find effective solutions is part of the test.</li>
    <li>There are plugins that might make this easier. Your ability to know what they are or figure out what they are is part of the test.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>This test runs on an ember-cli-mirage server. It is self-contained, and if you are seeing this page, already running.</p>

  <p>There is an api '/api/customers'. It takes one query param, 'query'. So a sample request from your widget would be:</p>

  <pre class="code">
    GET /api/customers?query=bob
  </pre>

  <p>You need to provide the infrastructure to make the requests and manage the data in ember. Please do use ember-data to complete the task.</p>
